-- Citic Bank International Said to Sell 500 Million Yuan of Fixed-Rate Notes
-- Shelley Smith
-- 2010-07-06T09:43:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/citic-bank-international-said-to-sell-500-million-yuan-of-fixed-rate-notes.html

          
          
                  July 6 (Bloomberg) --  Citic Bank International Ltd.  sold
500 million yuan of fixed-rate certificates of deposit,
according to a person familiar with the matter.  
 HSBC Holdings Plc managed the sale of the 2.68 percent
notes due 2011, said the person, who declined to be identified
because the details are private.  
          
          


  


        